{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/mastering-paper/paper-3-features/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"New Paper for iOS 3.0 features I can't live without","date":"2015-09-11T00:00:00.000Z","date_pretty":"September 11th, 2015","date_from_now":"5 years ago","last_modified_at":"2019-09-13T16:03:03.000Z","last_modified_at_from_now":"10 months ago","path":"/mastering-paper/paper-3-features/","author":null,"excerpt":"Paper for iOS comes to the iPhone with productivity boosting features like photo import, text notes, grid view, rotate, and more.","tags":["Paper for iOS","Apple"],"image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"aspectRatio":2.455357142857143,"src":"/static/ad1699adbfa67ea201a57079d9adfc90/fc20c/paper-3-feature.jpg","srcSet":"/static/ad1699adbfa67ea201a57079d9adfc90/6e883/paper-3-feature.jpg 275w,\n/static/ad1699adbfa67ea201a57079d9adfc90/a09ef/paper-3-feature.jpg 550w,\n/static/ad1699adbfa67ea201a57079d9adfc90/fc20c/paper-3-feature.jpg 1100w,\n/static/ad1699adbfa67ea201a57079d9adfc90/9352a/paper-3-feature.jpg 1600w","sizes":"(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px"},"fixed":{"src":"/static/ad1699adbfa67ea201a57079d9adfc90/fc20c/paper-3-feature.jpg","height":450,"width":1100}}},"toc":true,"comments":true,"comments_locked":true,"hide_meta":null},"id":"827d4cd7-4241-596c-986d-f0a6b5f41126","html":"<p>The hashtag <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/createanywhere\">#CreateAnywhere</a> takes on greater meaning now that <a href=\"http://www.fiftythree.com/paper\"><strong>Paper by FiftyThree</strong></a> is available for iPhone — a device I <em>always have with me</em>. Not only that, but with a new set of tricks up its sleeve, Paper is quickly becoming a productivity powerhouse.</p>\n<p>Here’s some of my favorite additions found in the 3.0 update…</p>\n<h2 id=\"universal-paper-app\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#universal-paper-app\" aria-label=\"universal paper app permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Universal Paper App</h2>\n<p>Yes, you’ve read correctly — Paper is now a universal iOS app that works on both iPad and iPhone. Every time I open Paper on my iPhone 5s I’m amazed that the features found on the iPad version all made the journey over.</p>\n<p>Much like the complete UI overhaul in <a href=\"http://news.fiftythree.com/post/79379441335/the-paper-ios-7-update-is-here-brighter-fresher\">version 1.6.1</a>, I got the sense that the team at FiftyThree re-evaluated every bit of the app for 3.0. Even if that meant modifying Paper’s defining characteristics<sup id=\"fnref-1\"><a href=\"#fn-1\" class=\"footnote-ref\">1</a></sup> to make the experience more intuitive and fluid.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 900px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 54.18181818181819%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\"\n        alt=\"Paper 3.0 App Store screenshot\"\n        title=\"Paper 3.0 App Store screenshot\"\n        data-src=\"/static/1da41bcaac85a23bf277482d07515849/062c0/paper-3-store.jpg\"\n        data-srcset=\"/static/1da41bcaac85a23bf277482d07515849/16841/paper-3-store.jpg 275w,\n/static/1da41bcaac85a23bf277482d07515849/50c97/paper-3-store.jpg 550w,\n/static/1da41bcaac85a23bf277482d07515849/062c0/paper-3-store.jpg 900w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"importing-images\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#importing-images\" aria-label=\"importing images permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Importing images</h2>\n<p>Love it or hate it (stick me in the love it camp), you can finally import images into Paper by FiftyThree! Tap the camera icon and you can either snap a picture or choose one from your photo library to place on the canvas.</p>\n<p>You are limited to one photo per idea — but you can scale it, rotate it, and even call-out an area of interest with a new <a href=\"http://blog.fiftythree.com/posts/annotate-spotlight-photos\"><em>Spotlight option</em></a>.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 900px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 51.63636363636363%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\"\n        alt=\"Importing photos into Paper 3.0\"\n        title=\"Importing photos into Paper 3.0\"\n        data-src=\"/static/b12bd0d05a111d5a4bd4fc146a5aeac3/062c0/paper-3-photo-import.jpg\"\n        data-srcset=\"/static/b12bd0d05a111d5a4bd4fc146a5aeac3/16841/paper-3-photo-import.jpg 275w,\n/static/b12bd0d05a111d5a4bd4fc146a5aeac3/50c97/paper-3-photo-import.jpg 550w,\n/static/b12bd0d05a111d5a4bd4fc146a5aeac3/062c0/paper-3-photo-import.jpg 900w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>I’m excited to use this feature as a sketching aid — drawing directly on reference images I’ve imported into Paper. There’s no way to toggle this layer off yet (<em>psst… FiftyThree engineers if you’re reading</em>), but it’s easy enough to remove if you want to leave behind just what you’ve drawn or painted.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/439a7a93de5c72943462e53960340917/paper-3-clear-photo.gif\" alt=\"Clear Photo layer animation\"></p>\n<p>Tap and hold on the Eraser tool, tap <strong>Clear Photo</strong>, and poof!</p>\n<h2 id=\"rotating-ideas\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#rotating-ideas\" aria-label=\"rotating ideas permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Rotating ideas</h2>\n<p>What a time saver this one is. If you wanted to share ideas “right side up” you had to export to the camera roll to make the rotation edit. This worked OK for sharing on social media but not so much with drawings shared on Mix.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 900px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 19.636363636363637%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\"\n        alt=\"new rotate button in Paper 3.0\"\n        title=\"new rotate button in Paper 3.0\"\n        data-src=\"/static/b3aa37cec9bb9c4a37f187f8537ee889/062c0/paper-3-rotate-button.jpg\"\n        data-srcset=\"/static/b3aa37cec9bb9c4a37f187f8537ee889/16841/paper-3-rotate-button.jpg 275w,\n/static/b3aa37cec9bb9c4a37f187f8537ee889/50c97/paper-3-rotate-button.jpg 550w,\n/static/b3aa37cec9bb9c4a37f187f8537ee889/062c0/paper-3-rotate-button.jpg 900w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>In 3.0 there’s a new button conveniently located below each idea for rotating the canvas in 90 degree intervals. Horizontal and vertical ideas live in harmony together because of the new grid view. Which leads me to my next favorite thing in Paper 3.0…</p>\n<p>View ideas horizontally or vertically with the tap of the new <strong>rotate button</strong>.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 600px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 74.9090909090909%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\"\n        alt=\"Idea that hasn&#39;t been rotated yet\"\n        title=\"Idea that hasn&#39;t been rotated yet\"\n        data-src=\"/static/39114f757f4e44d288079f24ac43ac0a/f6133/paper-3-rotate-horizontal.jpg\"\n        data-srcset=\"/static/39114f757f4e44d288079f24ac43ac0a/16841/paper-3-rotate-horizontal.jpg 275w,\n/static/39114f757f4e44d288079f24ac43ac0a/50c97/paper-3-rotate-horizontal.jpg 550w,\n/static/39114f757f4e44d288079f24ac43ac0a/f6133/paper-3-rotate-horizontal.jpg 600w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 600px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 74.9090909090909%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\"\n        alt=\"Idea rotated 90 degrees\"\n        title=\"Idea rotated 90 degrees\"\n        data-src=\"/static/aa55956867ba81bb656585c4db180842/f6133/paper-3-rotate-vertically.jpg\"\n        data-srcset=\"/static/aa55956867ba81bb656585c4db180842/16841/paper-3-rotate-vertically.jpg 275w,\n/static/aa55956867ba81bb656585c4db180842/50c97/paper-3-rotate-vertically.jpg 550w,\n/static/aa55956867ba81bb656585c4db180842/f6133/paper-3-rotate-vertically.jpg 600w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 600px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 74.9090909090909%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\"\n        alt=\"How rotated images appear in Paper&#39;s spaces\"\n        title=\"How rotated images appear in Paper&#39;s spaces\"\n        data-src=\"/static/95e18865a31e40e87eb9f5d752c1c647/f6133/paper-3-rotate-spaces.jpg\"\n        data-srcset=\"/static/95e18865a31e40e87eb9f5d752c1c647/16841/paper-3-rotate-spaces.jpg 275w,\n/static/95e18865a31e40e87eb9f5d752c1c647/50c97/paper-3-rotate-spaces.jpg 550w,\n/static/95e18865a31e40e87eb9f5d752c1c647/f6133/paper-3-rotate-spaces.jpg 600w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"journals-replaced-with-spaces\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#journals-replaced-with-spaces\" aria-label=\"journals replaced with spaces permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Journals replaced with “Spaces”</h2>\n<p>Paging through Paper’s digital journals might have been a good idea years ago, but with page counts in the hundreds it becomes unusable. Journals transitioning into “Spaces” is one of the best things to happen to Paper since the introduction of <a href=\"https://www.fiftythree.com/think\"><strong>Think Kit</strong></a>.</p>\n<p>Instead of ideas bound together as books, they’re presented with a different UI metaphor — stacks of paper. These stacks expand into an aligned grid of cards you can interact with when tapped on.</p>\n<p>I’ll tell you this much, scrolling through ideas in this way sure beats flipping back 500 plus pages to find a drawing I worked on a year ago.</p>\n<p><div class=\"gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper\" style=\"padding-bottom: 56.42857142857143%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden; \" > <div class=\"embedVideo-container\"> <iframe data-src=\"https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/VBMt_sjEXF4?rel=0\" class=\"embedVideo-iframe lazyload\" style=\"border:0; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; \" allowfullscreen></iframe> </div> </div></p>\n<p>These new “Spaces” are more accommodating of the new content types found in Paper 3.0 as well. Ideas in portrait or landscape orientation fit in perfectly with text notes and images.</p>\n<p>There’s <em>no way any of this would be usable</em> or look half as good as it does now if FiftyThree stuck with the book/journal motif.</p>\n<h2 id=\"other-new-additions\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#other-new-additions\" aria-label=\"other new additions permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Other new additions</h2>\n<p>In my short time with the new iPad and iPhone versions I’ve come across a couple of other refinements that should make the app more pleasant to use. Feel free to add any you’ve discovered in the comment section below.</p>\n<h3 id=\"popular-gestures-have-dedicated-buttons-now\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#popular-gestures-have-dedicated-buttons-now\" aria-label=\"popular gestures have dedicated buttons now permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Popular gestures have dedicated buttons now</h3>\n<p>Undoing mistakes and page management are some of the most common Paper actions I get questions about. In my experience most people had no clue you could do either — so I’m happy to see they’re more discoverable now.</p>\n<p>Undoing (Rewinding) can still be triggered with a gesture<sup id=\"fnref-2\"><a href=\"#fn-2\" class=\"footnote-ref\">2</a></sup> or by tapping the new <strong>&#x3C;&#x3C;</strong> button found in the tool tray. Tap the button to step back an edit at a time or hold down to speed it up.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 896px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 45.81818181818183%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\"\n        alt=\"Rewind button in tool tray\"\n        title=\"Rewind button in tool tray\"\n        data-src=\"/static/6e333f87cebe6c6b500b78afbd0ee721/968f2/paper-3-rewind-button.jpg\"\n        data-srcset=\"/static/6e333f87cebe6c6b500b78afbd0ee721/16841/paper-3-rewind-button.jpg 275w,\n/static/6e333f87cebe6c6b500b78afbd0ee721/50c97/paper-3-rewind-button.jpg 550w,\n/static/6e333f87cebe6c6b500b78afbd0ee721/968f2/paper-3-rewind-button.jpg 896w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 896px) 100vw, 896px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<div class=\"custom-block notice\"><div class=\"custom-block-heading\">ProTip: quick undo gesture</div><div class=\"custom-block-body\"><p>To quickly undo a mistake double tap the screen with two fingers.</p></div></div>\n<p>The <strong>• • •</strong> button below each idea allows you to delete, duplicate, and move pages now. You no longer have to tap and hold an idea with one hand and do finger gymnastics with the other to move things around.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 1100px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 19.636363636363637%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\"\n        alt=\"more button\"\n        title=\"more button\"\n        data-src=\"/static/832719a380ba7b7061f0a58c8688bd29/eacc7/paper-3-more-button.jpg\"\n        data-srcset=\"/static/832719a380ba7b7061f0a58c8688bd29/16841/paper-3-more-button.jpg 275w,\n/static/832719a380ba7b7061f0a58c8688bd29/50c97/paper-3-more-button.jpg 550w,\n/static/832719a380ba7b7061f0a58c8688bd29/eacc7/paper-3-more-button.jpg 1100w,\n/static/832719a380ba7b7061f0a58c8688bd29/ad1db/paper-3-more-button.jpg 1182w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h3 id=\"ability-to-annotate-ideas-and-create-text-notes\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#ability-to-annotate-ideas-and-create-text-notes\" aria-label=\"ability to annotate ideas and create text notes permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Ability to annotate ideas and create text notes</h3>\n<p>Perfect for to-do lists, recipes, or adding captions to your ideas and photos. I could see this coming in handy for providing context around an idea you’ve shared or to solicit feedback from followers.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 640px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 70.54545454545455%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\"\n        alt=\"text notes in Paper\"\n        title=\"text notes in Paper\"\n        data-src=\"/static/02d54efc3cf32e5d68451c25e5e294e7/312de/paper-3-text-ideas.jpg\"\n        data-srcset=\"/static/02d54efc3cf32e5d68451c25e5e294e7/16841/paper-3-text-ideas.jpg 275w,\n/static/02d54efc3cf32e5d68451c25e5e294e7/50c97/paper-3-text-ideas.jpg 550w,\n/static/02d54efc3cf32e5d68451c25e5e294e7/312de/paper-3-text-ideas.jpg 640w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>Basic formatting of text can be achieved by <a href=\"http://blog.fiftythree.com/posts/swipe-to-style\">swiping across text</a> to cycle through styles (Title, Subtitle, Bullet, and Sub-Bullet). You can also <strong>bold</strong>, <em>italicize</em>, and <s>strikethrough</s> text by selecting it and tapping the right arrow followed by <strong>Style</strong>.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 900px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 74.9090909090909%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\"\n        alt=\"styling text in Paper 3.0\"\n        title=\"styling text in Paper 3.0\"\n        data-src=\"/static/cb56daedc172bfa347428983c4e83a15/062c0/paper-3-text-styles.jpg\"\n        data-srcset=\"/static/cb56daedc172bfa347428983c4e83a15/16841/paper-3-text-styles.jpg 275w,\n/static/cb56daedc172bfa347428983c4e83a15/50c97/paper-3-text-styles.jpg 550w,\n/static/cb56daedc172bfa347428983c4e83a15/062c0/paper-3-text-styles.jpg 900w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h4 id=\"changing-the-default-idea-type\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#changing-the-default-idea-type\" aria-label=\"changing the default idea type permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Changing the default idea type</h4>\n<p>You can switch between idea types (Canvas/Photo/Text) by tapping their corresponding icons in the tool tray. But you can also change which type is used as the default when creating a new idea.</p>\n<figure>\n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 640px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 52.36363636363636%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\" alt=\"change default idea type\" title=\"change default idea type\" data-src=\"/static/78f8efbe006a4cd5e1706aba8563827b/312de/paper-3-idea-type-button.jpg\" data-srcset=\"/static/78f8efbe006a4cd5e1706aba8563827b/16841/paper-3-idea-type-button.jpg 275w,\n/static/78f8efbe006a4cd5e1706aba8563827b/50c97/paper-3-idea-type-button.jpg 550w,\n/static/78f8efbe006a4cd5e1706aba8563827b/312de/paper-3-idea-type-button.jpg 640w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n  <figcaption><p>Tap and hold on the new idea button (in this example it&apos;s a squiggle) at the bottom of the screen and select which type (Canvas, Photo, Text) you want to use as the default.</p></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<h3 id=\"formerly-known-as-mix\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#formerly-known-as-mix\" aria-label=\"formerly known as mix permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Formerly known As Mix</h3>\n<p>Mix is no longer something you “pull down” to access from within Paper. The stream of ideas from the <strong>People You Follow</strong> on Mix (or should I say PAPER now?) now appear alongside your private spaces for quicker access.</p>\n<div class=\"custom-block notice\"><div class=\"custom-block-heading\">ProTip: see all your shared ideas</div><div class=\"custom-block-body\"><p>The <em>shared journal</em> has been removed from Paper but you can still see all of your public ideas in one place. Tap your avatar in the upper right, and then tap your name to bring up your profile card. From here tap <strong>Ideas</strong> to see everything you’ve shared.</p></div></div>\n<p>OK, back to lusting over the new <strong>Apple Pencil</strong> and waiting for the day Apple brings that technology to the smaller and cheaper iPads.</p>\n<div class=\"footnotes\">\n<hr>\n<ol>\n<li id=\"fn-1\">\n<p>Yes the journal book view and zoom loupe have gone away. Change is good, deal with it.</p>\n<a href=\"#fnref-1\" class=\"footnote-backref\">↩</a>\n</li>\n<li id=\"fn-2\">\n<p>A small adjustment was made to the way Rewind works. To trigger it tap once with 2 fingers anywhere on the screen before making the <a href=\"/mastering-paper/introduction-tool-guide/#gestures-to-master\">circle gesture</a>.</p>\n<a href=\"#fnref-2\" class=\"footnote-backref\">↩</a>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</div>","excerpt":"The hashtag #CreateAnywhere takes on greater meaning now that Paper by FiftyThree is available for iPhone — a device I always have with me…","timeToRead":5,"tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/mastering-paper/paper-3-features/#universal-paper-app\">Universal Paper App</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/mastering-paper/paper-3-features/#importing-images\">Importing images</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/mastering-paper/paper-3-features/#rotating-ideas\">Rotating ideas</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/mastering-paper/paper-3-features/#journals-replaced-with-spaces\">Journals replaced with “Spaces”</a></li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"/mastering-paper/paper-3-features/#other-new-additions\">Other new additions</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/mastering-paper/paper-3-features/#popular-gestures-have-dedicated-buttons-now\">Popular gestures have dedicated buttons now</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/mastering-paper/paper-3-features/#ability-to-annotate-ideas-and-create-text-notes\">Ability to annotate ideas and create text notes</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/mastering-paper/paper-3-features/#formerly-known-as-mix\">Formerly known As Mix</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>"},"comments":{"edges":[{"node":{"id":"64e9328a-1291-5695-9f11-6e8746164e37","frontmatter":{"name":"Nancy","email":null,"friendlyDate":"September 17, 2015","iso8601Date":"2015-09-17T13:26:21.000Z","published":null},"html":"<p>Thank you for this review! Usually, I just pick up the new features as I stumble\nacross them and then play with how I might use them. I found your MASTERING\nPAPER series last year and became an avid (silent) fan…* : )</p>"}},{"node":{"id":"46d53f6a-60a0-5b74-9d1d-88603b5bf3c5","frontmatter":{"name":"Sophie Lynn","email":null,"friendlyDate":"October 14, 2015","iso8601Date":"2015-10-14T18:28:35.000Z","published":null},"html":"<p>Wow! This review is amazing! Looks like I haven’t got the best of it out yet~</p>"}},{"node":{"id":"e52f0e8c-4843-596d-8ab4-eeb2641c9b5f","frontmatter":{"name":"Sel Orm","email":null,"friendlyDate":"January 01, 2016","iso8601Date":"2016-01-01T08:42:15.000Z","published":null},"html":"<p>I owe you a debt of gratitude for this blog, but I’ll come right out and say\nthat this sounds like sponsored PR hogwash to me. When I got my fifty three\npencil I decided to learn how to draw all over again more naturally (without\nlayers).</p>\n<p>I’d had paper before the pencil, I’d used it before and it was great, but\npairing Paper with pencil took the experience to a whole new level. Making\nstrokes with the tip, flipping it over to erase, blending and even using palm\ngrip (I’d never used palm grip in my life. Not even with real pencils) and then\nthere was the time you could export and get your journal printed. How awesome\nwas that? Say what you will about the journals, they are most impressive (And\nreally? You’d draw in the same journal for a year?) Paper didn’t feel like an\napp. It felt like…Paper. Real paper. Now all that is gone, and it’s been\nreplaced by this…ordinary note taking app which is fine (because I found a\nbacked up older version and reinstalled it).</p>\n<p>My point I do not believe there’s an artist alive who experienced the magic of\npaper and is excited by features that existed in MS paint. The new features are\nmore geared towards note taking than artistic expression - spotlight, annotation\netc… Paper is not paper anymore. It’s just another soulless app. A big big\nshame.</p>"}},{"node":{"id":"6ec74078-7fd3-55f1-a3c1-8ae973f2cdcf","frontmatter":{"name":"Michael Rose","email":"1ce71bc10b86565464b612093d89707e","friendlyDate":"January 01, 2016","iso8601Date":"2016-01-01T17:39:33.000Z","published":null},"html":"<p>Agree about all the note taking features added, I use none of them and prefer\nmore powerful apps like Evernote for that sort of thing.</p>\n<p>The journal UI switch is a matter of preference I think. I don’t disagree that\nPaper had some growing pains when 3.0 launched, but most of those have been\naddressed in recent updates. I personally like to organize my thousands of\nsketches into a few journals vs. hundreds of smaller journals.</p>\n<p>I accept that I’m not the norm since I seriously doubt the average Paper user\nhas as many sketches as I have. Being able to scroll throw a grid view to find\nsomething is way more usable to me then the old tedious way of flipping page by\npage. And even if I broke a journal of 100+ pages into several smaller ones you\nnow have the added problem of remembering what journal you stuck a sketch in.</p>\n<p>And that’s not even addressing the problems with the old journals and how they’d\noften accidentally flip to a new page when drawing near the canvas’ edge. Sure\nthe Moleskine look is gone but if you ask me that was a necessary change to make\nthe app usable on both iPad and iPhone.</p>\n<p>At the end of the day I care most about how the actual pens, pencil, and\nwatercolor tools function. None of that was messed with. Everything else is\neither icing on the cake or a distraction depending on your perspective. If you\ndon’t like the social stuff don’t use it, note taking and picture import…\ndon’t use it.</p>\n<p>I get why people are upset with the core stuff being changed or removed, but the\naddition of new tools and features? Not a big deal if you ask me.</p>\n<p>That’s a bummer on the Book printing feature being killed. I wrongly assumed it\nwas still available since there’s an option to “Print Book” when in journal\nview, but it just goes to a currently unavailable page. Not sure if that’s\npermanent or what.</p>"}}]}},"pageContext":{"next":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/procreate-paintings/jordan-s-portrait/","title":"Blushing my cheeks","categories":["procreate-paintings"],"tags":["Procreate","portrait","illustration","time lapse","Sktchy"]},"fileAbsolutePath":"/home/28041/opensource/github.com/mmistakes/made-mistakes-gatsby/src/posts/procreate-paintings/jordan-s-portrait.md"},"previous":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/procreate-paintings/jenell-d-portrait/","title":"Don't play with soot","categories":["procreate-paintings"],"tags":["Procreate","portrait","illustration","time lapse","Sktchy","black and white"]},"fileAbsolutePath":"/home/28041/opensource/github.com/mmistakes/made-mistakes-gatsby/src/posts/procreate-paintings/jenell-d-portrait.md"}}}}